{"id":1534,"date":"2018-04-05T15:52:16","date_gmt":"2018-04-05T19:52:16","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.canadianchopinsociety.com\/?page_id=1534"},"modified":"2019-02-01T15:27:17","modified_gmt":"2019-02-01T20:27:17","slug":"scholarship","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/www.canadianchopinsociety.com\/scholarship","title":{"rendered":"Scholarship"},"content":{"rendered":"<h1>The Canadian Chopin Society Scholarship Program<\/h1>\n<p>The Canadian Chopin Society Scholarship Program provides support and encouragement for young pianists to expand their repertoire and deepen their understanding of the music of Chopin.<\/p>\n<p>Scholarships of $1000 will be awarded each year on a competitive basis to outstanding Canadian pianists who demonstrate a special affinity for the music of Chopin, and the potential to participate in both the Senior Division of the Canadian Chopin Piano Competition and the International F. Chopin Competition.<\/p>\n<p>The Scholarship Program is open to qualified Canadian pianists (Canadian citizens or permanent residents) born between 1995 and 2004.<\/p>\n<p>Pianists wishing to apply for the scholarship are invited to submit an application and video, along with a brief personal statement outlining the significance of the music of Chopin in their musical development, and a letter of recommendation from their current teacher.<\/p>\n<h2><strong>Repertoire Requirements<\/strong><\/h2>\n<p><strong>One of the following works:<\/strong><br \/>\nBallade in G minor, op. 23<br \/>\nBallade in F major, op. 38<br \/>\nBallade in A flat major, op. 47<br \/>\nBallade in F minor, op. 52<br \/>\nBarcarolle in F sharp major, op. 60<br \/>\nFantasy in F minor, op. 49<br \/>\n<strong>AND<\/strong><strong><br \/>\n<\/strong><strong>One of the following works:<\/strong><br \/>\nAndante Spianato and Polonaise in E flat major, op. 22<br \/>\nPolonaise in F sharp minor, op. 44<br \/>\nPolonaise in A flat major, op. 53<br \/>\nPolonaises op. 26 no. 1 <strong>and<\/strong> no. 2<\/p>\n<p><strong>Deadline to apply: February 15, 2019<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><a id=\"applicationform\" name=\"applicationform\"><\/a>The application form, letter of reference and link to the video recording must be submitted, together with a non-refundable application fee of $25 to <a href=\"mailto:info@canadianchopinsociety.com\">info@canadianchopinsociety.com<\/a>.<\/p>\n<div role=\"form\" class=\"wpcf7\" id=\"wpcf7-f1729-o1\" lang=\"en-US\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<div class=\"screen-reader-response\"><p role=\"status\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-atomic=\"true\"><\/p> <ul><\/ul><\/div>\n<form action=\"\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1534#wpcf7-f1729-o1\" method=\"post\" class=\"wpcf7-form init\" novalidate=\"novalidate\" data-status=\"init\">\n<div style=\"display: none;\">\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7\" value=\"1729\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_version\" value=\"5.4.1\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_locale\" value=\"en_US\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_unit_tag\" value=\"wpcf7-f1729-o1\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_container_post\" value=\"0\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_posted_data_hash\" value=\"\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_recaptcha_response\" value=\"\" \/>\n<\/div>\n<h2>Your Information<\/h2>\n<div class=\"label\"><label for=\"fname\">First Name<span class=\"red\">*<\/span><\/label><\/div>\n<div class=\"input\"><span class=\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap fname\"><input type=\"text\" name=\"fname\" value=\"\" size=\"40\" class=\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required text\" aria-required=\"true\" aria-invalid=\"false\" \/><\/span><\/div>\n<div class=\"clear\"><\/div>\n<div class=\"label\"><label for=\"lname\">Last Name<span class=\"red\">*<\/span><\/label><\/div>\n<div class=\"input\"><span class=\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap lname\"><input type=\"text\" name=\"lname\" value=\"\" size=\"40\" class=\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-text wpcf7-validates-as-required